The paper focuses on adversarial attacks against deep learning systems in the context of medical imaging tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of healthcare systems and the potential for fraud, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of considering the human factors in healthcare, which could be relevant to the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
